      <body>
         <head>To <persName><ptr target="/persons/pers1793.xml"/>Sarah Ryan</persName><note
               place="foot" n="1"/>Possibly replying to <persName><ptr
                  target="/persons/pers1793.xml"/>Ryan</persName>&apos;s letter of <date
               when="1758-03-20">Mar. 20</date>.</head>
         <opener><placeName>Dublin</placeName><lb/><date when="1758-04-04">April 4, 1758</date><lb/><lb/>
            <salute>My Dear Sister,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>Oh that I could be of some use to you! I long to help you forward in your way. I want to
            have your understanding a mere lamp of light, always shining with light from above! I
            want you to be full of divine knowledge and wisdom, as <index indexName="biblical">
               <term cRef="Josh3:15">Jordan in the time of harvest</term>
            </index>.<note place="foot" n="2">See <index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="Josh3:15">Josh. 3:15</term>
               </index></note> I want your words to be full of grace, <index indexName="biblical">
               <term cRef="Matt26:7">poured out as precious ointment</term>
            </index>.<note place="foot" n="3">See <index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="Matt26:7">Matt. 26:7</term>
               </index>.</note> I want your every work to bear the stamp of God, to be <index
               indexName="biblical">
               <term cRef="Eph5:2 Phil4:18">a sacrifice of a sweet-smelling savour</term>
            </index>,<note place="foot" n="4">See <index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="Eph5:2">Eph. 5:2</term>
               </index>; <index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="Phil4:18">Phil. 4:18</term>
               </index>.</note> without any part weak, earthly or human, all holy, all divine! The
            great God, your Father and your love, bring you to this self-same thing! Begin, soldier
            of Christ, child of God! <index indexName="biblical">
               <term cRef="Eph4:1">Walk worthy of the vocation wherewith thou art called</term>
            </index>!<note place="foot" n="5"><index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="Eph4:1">Eph. 4:1</term>
               </index>.</note> Remember the faith! Remember <index indexName="biblical">
               <term cRef="Heb2:10">the Captain of thy salvation</term>
            </index>!<note place="foot" n="6"><index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="Heb2:10">Heb. 2:10</term>
               </index>.</note> Fight! Conquer! Dieâ€”and live for ever!</p>
         <closer>I am,<lb/>
            <signed>Yours, etc.,<lb/><persName>J.W.</persName></signed></closer>
      </body>
